They appeared along with a civilian accomplice who pretended to be a police inspector. The five also allegedly assaulted other police officers while they were resisting arrest. The officers are Manager William (30), Brian Mzilikazi (33), Natasha Mupingo (32) and Tafuma Ruvuke (32) while their accomplice is Bigboy Mjenda (32). The five waylaid, assaulted and robbed at least one motorist along Mazowe-Centenary Road. The four police officers are from Harare, while Mjenda is from Ruwa. They appeared before Bindura provincial Magistrate Tinashe Ndokera facing robbery and assault charges and were remanded on bail to November 17 for trial. --Herald--